menu "ESP-Brookesia: Settings App Configurations"
    config BROOKESIA_APP_SETTINGS_WIFI_MAX_VISIBLE_APS
        int "Wi-Fi AP list page size"
        range 1 30
        default 5
        help
            Number of saved or scanned Wi-Fi access point rows shown per page in Settings.
            Scan results are kept as a full list and paged in the UI.

    config BROOKESIA_APP_SETTINGS_ENABLE_MEMORY_TRACE
        bool "Enable Settings memory/heap trace logs (profiling)"
        default n
        help
            When enabled, the Settings app emits [HeapTrace] logs while populating the
            Wi-Fi network lists (e.g. settings.sync_wifi slot accounting). Profiling aid
            only; keep disabled in production builds.
endmenu
